EventCorefBank (ECB) -- release 1.0 --
======================================

Overview
--------
This corpus consists of a collection of Google News documents annotated 
with within- and cross-document event coreference information. The documents
are grouped according to the Google News Cluster, each group of documents
representing the same seminal event (or topic). 



Acknowledgments
---------------
Many thanks to Andy Hickl for his help in the annotation process of this resource.



ECB 1.0 Statistics
------------------
within-document events: 1302
within-topic events: 339
cross-document events: 208
event mentions: 1744
documents: 482
topics: 43



The annotation scheme for ECB is described in:
---------------------------------------------
[-] Cosmin Adrian Bejan and Sanda Harabagiu. A Linguistic Resource for Discovering Event Structures and Resolving Event Coreference. LREC'08.

[-] Cosmin Adrian Bejan. Learning Event Structures from Text. PhD Thesis, The University of Texas at Dallas, 2009.



The papers that use this corpus:
--------------------------------
[-] Cosmin Adrian Bejan and Sanda Harabagiu. Unsupervised Event Coreference Resolution with Rich Linguistic Features. ACL'10.

[-] Cosmin Adrian Bejan, Matthew Titsworth, Andy Hickl, and Sanda Harabagiu. Nonparametric Bayesian Models for Unsupervised Event Coreference Resolution. NIPS'09.

[-] Cosmin Adrian Bejan. Learning Event Structures from Text. PhD Thesis, The University of Texas at Dallas, 2009.



